
[1]moralizing

   MOR'ALIZING, ppr. Applying to a moral purpose, or explaining in a moral
   sense.

   1. Making moral reflections in words or writing.

     MOR'ALIZING, n. The application of facts to a moral purpose, or the
                        making of moral reflections.

   His moralizings are always pleasant, and he does not spare, where he
   thinks it useful to moralize.
     __________________________________________________________________

